Search Criteria:

Winter Quarter, 2021      Currently in week 5.


   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

                              Academic English
       _________________________________________________________________

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Course Codes 20000 - 20009:
  ~ You must enroll in the AC ENG 20A lab (20106)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Ac Eng 20 courses:
  ~ Students are required to take the Academic English
  ~     Placement Test prior to enrolling in AC ENG 20
  ~     courses. Dates of the placement test can be
  ~     obtained by contacting the UCI Academic Testing
  ~     Center at (949) 824-6207, or testcenter@uci.edu,
  ~     or via their web site at
  ~     http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/XRLDYaofX7ovQs63BPTo to be cleared to enroll in ###
   ###  the desired course.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-units initially, ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. if you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/tyn2C5GiXLcCDfPsvmRC The School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences will wait to process requests until the 18-unit cap is  ###
   ###  lifted. No exceptions.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Friday, DECEMBER 11th by 3PM.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction,  ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###                 Claire Trevor School of the Arts                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Claire Trevor School   ###
   ###  of the Arts is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD:  The deadline to add courses in the Claire Trevor School of ###
   ###  the Arts is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  After these dates, requests to Add/Drop are considered through   ###
   ###  petition based on extenuating circumstances, requiring the       ###
   ###  approval of the Dean of the school offering the course as well   ###
   ###  as the Dean of the student's major. Enrollment Exception is      ###
   ###  available on Student Access.                                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Please contact the faculty member directly for courses listed    ###
   ###  with a "B" (Authorization Code) restriction.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Major and repeat restrictions for some courses will be removed   ###
   ###  beginning at noon on December 14, 2020.                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                     Art

        Enrolled students must attend the first day of instruction.
        Enrolled students who do not attend or are late for the first
        day of instruction, may be dropped from the course at the
        instructor's discretion.  Students will be responsible for
        officially dropping the course.

        Course material fees are non-refundable,unless the class is
        dropped AND the student notifies the Art administrative office
        by the MONDAY OF WEEK 3. Fees will not be refunded beyond the
        Monday Week 3; no exceptions. If a student drops the course
        beyond Week 3, the student will still be held accountable for
        paying the course material fee.

        Students who wish to waive the optional course material fee must
        inform the instructor with justification AND notify the Art
        administrative office by the MONDAY OF WEEK 3. Fees will not be
        waived beyond the Monday of Week 3; no exceptions.

        Students are welcome to enroll in courses when the major
        restrictions are removed; see above for the date/time when major
        restrictions will be removed. If classes are full, students are
        encouraged to enroll in the Wait List, if available. Students on
        the Wait List are advised to attend the first day of class.
        Students on the Wait List who do not attend the first day of
        class may lose the chance to be attended in the class.

        Instructors will give "add" and "drop" codes through the second
        week of classes, based on availability.
       _________________________________________________________________

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                             Biological Sciences

        SCHOOL/MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: All BIO SCI courses will initially be
        RESTRICTED to majors in the School of Biological Sciences ONLY.
        Note that some courses may be additionally restricted to
        specific majors. These major specific restrictions will lift
        (with the exception of major specific seminar courses) December
        4th by noon and at that point will be available to all majors
        within the School of Biological Sciences.

        For students NOT in the School of Biological Sciences, the
        school major restriction will lift December 18th by noon.

        REPEAT RESTRICTIONS: Students who wish to enroll to repeat a
        core, upper-division elective, or lab course will be restricted
        from enrolling until noon on December 18th.

        PREREQUISITES:  Students who have completed the equivalent of
        the prerequisites at another institution may become eligible to
        enroll in a particular UCI Bio Sci course by completing the form
        on the Bio Sci Student Affairs website:
        http://www.bio.uci.edu/students/undergraduates/course-pre-requisite-clearance-form/
        a minimum of two days before their window opens. Once students
        have had their prerequisites cleared they will remain eligible
        for one quarter, with the exception of Bio 199 (clearance
        remains for the academic year).

        LAB COURSES:

        BIO LAB ENROLLMENT POLICY!!!!

        THERE WILL BE NO DROPS ALLOWED OF ANY BIO SCI UPPER-DIVISION
        LABS AFTER January 4th at 5pm.  This deadline is earlier than
        the School of Biological Sciences week 2 deadline. Students
        CANNOT SWAP/CHANGE the lab section they are enrolled in after
        the Week 1 drop deadline.  Labs CANNOT be added if you have not
        attended the first meeting. You will need to speak to an
        Academic Counselor for assistance adding into an open lab during
        weeks 1 and 2 of the quarter only if you have attended all
        meetings.

        LAB FEES ARE NON-REFUNDABLE.
       _________________________________________________________________

  ~ Must complete and submit Packet B prior to
  ~     enrollment. Packet B available at:
  ~     http://www.bio.uci.edu/students/undergraduates/research/
  ~ ATTENTION: Maximum 5 units per quarter for all
  ~     independent study courses taken under the School
  ~     of Biological Sciences. Student must be in good
  ~     academic standing.
  ~ The deadline to submit Bio Sci 199 Packet B is Friday
  ~     of Week 2 by noon. NO EXCEPTIONS.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the response General Catalogue under each course     ###
   ###  description. Most major restrictions will be lifted on a rolling ###
   ###  basis. Major restrictions will be removed/lifted AFTER the fee   ###
   ###  deadline. The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the   ###
   ###  right to maintain major restrictions on impacted courses. Check  ###
   ###  http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan for              ###
   ###  announcements.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite first, before          ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A.) If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form, and click submit. The       ###
   ###  student will receive a response within 3-5 business days from an ###
   ###  Academic Counselor.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate Engineering forms are located at                   ###
   ###  &lt;http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms&gt;                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE:Students earning a deficient grade in a          ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped after the    ###
   ###  first week of class.  Students should address any prior grade    ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE: If you encounter an enrollment        ###
   ###  problem please email engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule       ###
   ###  updates, restriction changes, and changes to course capacities   ###
   ###  at http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the response General Catalogue under each course     ###
   ###  description. Most major restrictions will be lifted on a rolling ###
   ###  basis. Major restrictions will be removed/lifted AFTER the fee   ###
   ###  deadline. The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the   ###
   ###  right to maintain major restrictions on impacted courses. Check  ###
   ###  http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan for              ###
   ###  announcements.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite first, before          ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A.) If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form, and click submit. The       ###
   ###  student will receive a response within 3-5 business days from an ###
   ###  Academic Counselor.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate Engineering forms are located at                   ###
   ###  &lt;http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms&gt;                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE:Students earning a deficient grade in a          ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped after the    ###
   ###  first week of class.  Students should address any prior grade    ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE: If you encounter an enrollment        ###
   ###  problem please email engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule       ###
   ###  updates, restriction changes, and changes to course capacities   ###
   ###  at http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/XRLDYaofX7ovQs63BPTo to be cleared to enroll in ###
   ###  the desired course.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-units initially, ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. if you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/tyn2C5GiXLcCDfPsvmRC The School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences will wait to process requests until the 18-unit cap is  ###
   ###  lifted. No exceptions.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Friday, DECEMBER 11th by 3PM.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction,  ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###

                                  Chemistry

        Please visit the Chemistry Student Affairs website at
        https://www.chem.uci.edu/studentaffairs for additional
        information on Chemistry enrollment procedures and frequently
        asked questions. This includes information on repeat and major
        restrictions, important laboratory information, and how to clear
        your prerequisites.

        Classes are subject to change. Check the Schedule of Classes for
        possible changes before classes begin.

        Prerequisites and corequisites are actively checked. Click the
        "Prerequisite" link by each course for up-to-date requirements.

        There will be no changes to Chemistry labs after week 1. Please
        note: This deadline is earlier than the School of Physical
        Sciences week 2 deadline. Attendance for week 1 is mandatory.
        Lab Fees are non-refundable. Please see the Chemistry Student
        Affairs website at http://www.chem.uci.edu/studentaffairs for
        details. 

        If you don't meet the prerequisites for the course, you will be
        dropped from the course.

        Major restrictions will be lifted on Friday, December 18, by
        12:00pm. The repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,
        January 4, by 8:00am.

Chem course numbers 200 - 399:
  ~ Graduate Students: Choose the letter grade option for
  ~     the core graduate courses.  If you choose to take
  ~     an additional course for the S/U option, contact
  ~     the professor of the course.
  ~ Chem 299 enrollment requires permission from the
  ~     instructor.
  ~ Undergraduate Students who want to enroll in graduate
  ~     level courses:  Contact the faculty member to
  ~     obtain permission before your enrollment window
  ~     opens. Students will have access to the course on
  ~     WebReg once the instructor sends the notification
  ~     of approval to the Chemistry Student Affairs
  ~     (undergrad@chem.uci.edu).
  ~ Unauthorized students will be dropped from the
  ~     course.

    The column headings above are defined at:
	    https://www.reg.uci.edu/help/WebSoc-Columns.shtml

	    http://uci.bncollege.com

    A: Prerequisite required
    B: Authorization required
    C: Fee required
    K: Graduate only
    S: Satisfactory/unsatisfactory only
    X: Separate authorization codes required to add, drop, or change enrollment

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Chinese

        Students intending to enroll in a Chinese language class for the
        first time in Winter 2021 must complete an online placement
        assessment at http://humanities.uci.edu/placement/chinese

        For additional information, please contact Chinese Program at
        &lt;rhsieh@uci.edu&gt;.

        Students registered in any section of Chinese 1B/1MB, 2B, or 3B
        MUST ATTEND THE FIRST and SECOND class meeting of the course.
        Any student who does not meet this condition will be required to
        drop the class.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

   ###  the desired course.                                              ###

   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. if you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/tyn2C5GiXLcCDfPsvmRC The School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences will wait to process requests until the 18-unit cap is  ###
   ###  lifted. No exceptions.                                           ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Note that it is incumbent on the student to check the            ###
   ###  restriction status and seating availability of a course before   ###
   ###  registering or attempting to add or change their discussion/lb   ###
   ###  section enrollment.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINE TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS   ###
   ###  COURSES:                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Early deadline to add/drop/change    ###
   ###  grade option for any course specifically noted with a comment in ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an   ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  such courses.                                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: Deadline to add/drop/change grade    ###
   ###  option for all courses through WebReg. The Bren School of ICS    ###
   ###  STRICTLY adheres to and enforces this deadline for both          ###
   ###  undergraduate and graduate courses.                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2: The     ###
   ###  deadline to add/drop/change grade option is 5:00pm on Friday,    ###
   ###  January 15, 2021. After this deadline, students must submit an   ###
   ###  Enrollment Exception request online through Student Access.      ###
   ###  Exception requests will only be approved for extenuating and     ###
   ###  documented circumstances outside of the student's control.Fro    ###
   ###  more information:                                                ###
   ###  https://www.ics.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School WILL DROP ###
   ###  students who do not meet the required prerequisites from         ###
   ###  courses. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a course does   ###
   ###  not guarantee a seat in that course.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Priority for       ###
   ###  seating in undergraduate level courses is given first to         ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Graduate students seeking to enroll in   ###
   ###  an ICS undergraduate level course must submit a request to ICS   ###
   ###  Students Affairs. Note that approval is contingent on seating    ###
   ###  availability, and unauthorized students found enrolled in        ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Priority   ###
   ###  for seating in graduate level courses is given first to graduate ###
   ###  students. Undergraduate students seeking to enroll in an ICS     ###
   ###  graduate level course must obtain a written permission from the  ###
   ###  instructor before submitting a request for an authorization to   ###
   ###  ICS Student Affairs. Students should be aware that graduate      ###
   ###  level courses taken as an undergraduate will not count toward a  ###
   ###  graduate degree program.                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Students enrolling in courses through ###
   ###  Division of Continuing Education Programs may only request       ###
   ###  courses that show as "OPEN" in the Schedule of Classes. Approval ###
   ###  of requests is contingent on seating availability and            ###
   ###  prerequisite eligibility. For more information:                  ###
   ###  https://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                              Computer Science

        RESTRICTIONS: All COMPSCI courses will initially RESTRICTED to
        majors in the Donald Bren School of Information and Computer
        Sciences ONLY. Note that some courses may be additionally
        restricted to specific majors or level(s) of standing.

        Course restriction details and the restrictions update timeline
        for all ICS courses is published on the ICS Course Updates page
        (http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php).

        DISCUSSIONS &amp; LABS: Discussion and lab sections begin meeting
        AFTER the first lecture unless otherwise specified by the course
        instructor. Always check for messages from your instructors
        before the start of instruction.

        Some lab sections are scheduled in laptop instructional labs,
        ICS 364A, ICS2 162, or ICS2 170. Students enrolled in these labs
        are required to bring a personal laptop to class meetings.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain an authorization code.

   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  Friday Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social Ecology ###
   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL &amp; MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FIELD STUDY: Students are encouraged to begin planning for Field ###
   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following web site: ###
   ###  http://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-procedures      ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the response General Catalogue under each course     ###
   ###  description. Most major restrictions will be lifted on a rolling ###
   ###  basis. Major restrictions will be removed/lifted AFTER the fee   ###
   ###  deadline. The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the   ###
   ###  right to maintain major restrictions on impacted courses. Check  ###
   ###  http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan for              ###
   ###  announcements.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite first, before          ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A.) If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form, and click submit. The       ###
   ###  student will receive a response within 3-5 business days from an ###
   ###  Academic Counselor.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate Engineering forms are located at                   ###
   ###  &lt;http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms&gt;                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE:Students earning a deficient grade in a          ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped after the    ###
   ###  first week of class.  Students should address any prior grade    ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE: If you encounter an enrollment        ###
   ###  problem please email engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule       ###
   ###  updates, restriction changes, and changes to course capacities   ###
   ###  at http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

        Prerequisites in CSE courses are strictly enforced.

        All discussion and lab sections will begin AFTER the first
        lecture.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Note that it is incumbent on the student to check the            ###
   ###  restriction status and seating availability of a course before   ###
   ###  registering or attempting to add or change their discussion/lb   ###
   ###  section enrollment.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINE TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS   ###
   ###  COURSES:                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Early deadline to add/drop/change    ###
   ###  grade option for any course specifically noted with a comment in ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an   ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  such courses.                                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: Deadline to add/drop/change grade    ###
   ###  option for all courses through WebReg. The Bren School of ICS    ###
   ###  STRICTLY adheres to and enforces this deadline for both          ###
   ###  undergraduate and graduate courses.                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2: The     ###
   ###  deadline to add/drop/change grade option is 5:00pm on Friday,    ###
   ###  January 15, 2021. After this deadline, students must submit an   ###
   ###  Enrollment Exception request online through Student Access.      ###
   ###  Exception requests will only be approved for extenuating and     ###
   ###  documented circumstances outside of the student's control.Fro    ###
   ###  more information:                                                ###
   ###  https://www.ics.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School WILL DROP ###
   ###  students who do not meet the required prerequisites from         ###
   ###  courses. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a course does   ###
   ###  not guarantee a seat in that course.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Priority for       ###
   ###  seating in undergraduate level courses is given first to         ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Graduate students seeking to enroll in   ###
   ###  an ICS undergraduate level course must submit a request to ICS   ###
   ###  Students Affairs. Note that approval is contingent on seating    ###
   ###  availability, and unauthorized students found enrolled in        ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Priority   ###
   ###  for seating in graduate level courses is given first to graduate ###
   ###  students. Undergraduate students seeking to enroll in an ICS     ###
   ###  graduate level course must obtain a written permission from the  ###
   ###  instructor before submitting a request for an authorization to   ###
   ###  ICS Student Affairs. Students should be aware that graduate      ###
   ###  level courses taken as an undergraduate will not count toward a  ###
   ###  graduate degree program.                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Students enrolling in courses through ###
   ###  Division of Continuing Education Programs may only request       ###
   ###  courses that show as "OPEN" in the Schedule of Classes. Approval ###
   ###  of requests is contingent on seating availability and            ###
   ###  prerequisite eligibility. For more information:                  ###
   ###  https://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###                 Claire Trevor School of the Arts                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Claire Trevor School   ###
   ###  of the Arts is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD:  The deadline to add courses in the Claire Trevor School of ###
   ###  the Arts is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  After these dates, requests to Add/Drop are considered through   ###
   ###  petition based on extenuating circumstances, requiring the       ###
   ###  approval of the Dean of the school offering the course as well   ###
   ###  as the Dean of the student's major. Enrollment Exception is      ###
   ###  available on Student Access.                                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Please contact the faculty member directly for courses listed    ###
   ###  with a "B" (Authorization Code) restriction.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Major and repeat restrictions for some courses will be removed   ###
   ###  beginning at noon on December 14, 2020.                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/XRLDYaofX7ovQs63BPTo to be cleared to enroll in ###
   ###  the desired course.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-units initially, ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. if you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/tyn2C5GiXLcCDfPsvmRC The School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences will wait to process requests until the 18-unit cap is  ###
   ###  lifted. No exceptions.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Friday, DECEMBER 11th by 3PM.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction,  ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                  Economics

        Departmental drop/add policy

        Drops:

        Students may drop Economics courses only through the second week
        of the quarter.  After the second week, permission to drop will
        NOT be granted by the instructor.

        Adds:

        The Department Economics' policy on adds remains unchanged, and
        follows that of the School of Social Sciences.

        For more information please visit the website:
        http://www.economics.uci.edu/index.php?p=37
       _________________________________________________________________

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the response General Catalogue under each course     ###
   ###  description. Most major restrictions will be lifted on a rolling ###
   ###  basis. Major restrictions will be removed/lifted AFTER the fee   ###
   ###  deadline. The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the   ###
   ###  right to maintain major restrictions on impacted courses. Check  ###
   ###  http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan for              ###
   ###  announcements.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite first, before          ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A.) If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form, and click submit. The       ###
   ###  student will receive a response within 3-5 business days from an ###
   ###  Academic Counselor.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate Engineering forms are located at                   ###
   ###  &lt;http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms&gt;                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE:Students earning a deficient grade in a          ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped after the    ###
   ###  first week of class.  Students should address any prior grade    ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE: If you encounter an enrollment        ###
   ###  problem please email engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule       ###
   ###  updates, restriction changes, and changes to course capacities   ###
   ###  at http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the response General Catalogue under each course     ###
   ###  description. Most major restrictions will be lifted on a rolling ###
   ###  basis. Major restrictions will be removed/lifted AFTER the fee   ###
   ###  deadline. The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the   ###
   ###  right to maintain major restrictions on impacted courses. Check  ###
   ###  http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan for              ###
   ###  announcements.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite first, before          ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A.) If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form, and click submit. The       ###
   ###  student will receive a response within 3-5 business days from an ###
   ###  Academic Counselor.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate Engineering forms are located at                   ###
   ###  &lt;http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms&gt;                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE:Students earning a deficient grade in a          ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped after the    ###
   ###  first week of class.  Students should address any prior grade    ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE: If you encounter an enrollment        ###
   ###  problem please email engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule       ###
   ###  updates, restriction changes, and changes to course capacities   ###
   ###  at http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###

                                   English

        Students registered in any course offered by the Department of
        English are expected to attend both the FIRST and SECOND CLASS
        MEETINGS of the course or they may be required to drop the
        course.

        Please be advised that some English courses will have a "B" or
        "X" restriction starting on the first day of instruction.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.
