   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the response General Catalogue under each course     ###
   ###  description. Most major restrictions will be lifted on a rolling ###
   ###  basis. Major restrictions will be removed/lifted AFTER the fee   ###
   ###  deadline. The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the   ###
   ###  right to maintain major restrictions on impacted courses. Check  ###
   ###  http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan for              ###
   ###  announcements.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite first, before          ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A.) If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form, and click submit. The       ###
   ###  student will receive a response within 3-5 business days from an ###
   ###  Academic Counselor.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate Engineering forms are located at                   ###
   ###  &lt;http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms&gt;                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE:Students earning a deficient grade in a          ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped after the    ###
   ###  first week of class.  Students should address any prior grade    ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE: If you encounter an enrollment        ###
   ###  problem please email engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule       ###
   ###  updates, restriction changes, and changes to course capacities   ###
   ###  at http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

    A: Prerequisite required
    B: Authorization required
    D: Pass/not pass option only
    G: Lower-division only
    J: Upper-division only
    K: Graduate only
    L: Major only
    N: School major only
    S: Satisfactory/unsatisfactory only

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the response General Catalogue under each course     ###
   ###  description. Most major restrictions will be lifted on a rolling ###
   ###  basis. Major restrictions will be removed/lifted AFTER the fee   ###
   ###  deadline. The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the   ###
   ###  right to maintain major restrictions on impacted courses. Check  ###
   ###  http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan for              ###
   ###  announcements.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite first, before          ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A.) If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form, and click submit. The       ###
   ###  student will receive a response within 3-5 business days from an ###
   ###  Academic Counselor.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate Engineering forms are located at                   ###
   ###  &lt;http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms&gt;                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE:Students earning a deficient grade in a          ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped after the    ###
   ###  first week of class.  Students should address any prior grade    ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE: If you encounter an enrollment        ###
   ###  problem please email engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule       ###
   ###  updates, restriction changes, and changes to course capacities   ###
   ###  at http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the response General Catalogue under each course     ###
   ###  description. Most major restrictions will be lifted on a rolling ###
   ###  basis. Major restrictions will be removed/lifted AFTER the fee   ###
   ###  deadline. The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the   ###
   ###  right to maintain major restrictions on impacted courses. Check  ###
   ###  http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan for              ###
   ###  announcements.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite first, before          ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A.) If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form, and click submit. The       ###
   ###  student will receive a response within 3-5 business days from an ###
   ###  Academic Counselor.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate Engineering forms are located at                   ###
   ###  &lt;http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms&gt;                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE:Students earning a deficient grade in a          ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped after the    ###
   ###  first week of class.  Students should address any prior grade    ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE: If you encounter an enrollment        ###
   ###  problem please email engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule       ###
   ###  updates, restriction changes, and changes to course capacities   ###
   ###  at http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                           Film and Media Studies

        Film viewings take place in the studio sections. Attendance is
        mandatory. Enrollment in lecture and studio, or lecture and
        studio and discussion, where offered, is required for all Film &amp;
        Media Studies courses.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

        Campuswide Honors Collegium 1. FMS H80 class is restricted to
        students in the Campuswide Honors Collegium only. 2. Students in
        the Campuswide Honors Collegium must enroll in the class for a
        letter grade.

        There is a mandatory non-refundable lab fee of $20.00 for all
        Film &amp; Media Studies courses, including cross-listed and
        concurrently scheduled courses. Upon enrollment, lab fees are
        posted automatically to a student's ZOT Account. Students
        dropping before the second week drop deadline (January 15, 2021)
        may request a lab fee cancellation or refund in writing by
        contacting the Film &amp; Media Studies Lab Fee Administrator,
        Sylvia Meza-Tallada at Smezatal@uci.edu. No cancellation or
        refund will be made for an unpaid Lab Fee that goes to a
        collection agency.

        Due to the volume of majors and incoming new students,
        enrollment of all of Film and Media courses will be restricted
        to majors only unti Friday, December 4th, by noon.
       _________________________________________________________________

   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   French

        TO ENROLL IN A FRENCH LANGUAGE CLASS:

        For all French courses beyond 1A, placement testing is
        recommended, but not required for students who have successfully
        completed French classes in high school. Contact the UCI
        Academic Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu, (949) 824-6207,
        or visit their website at http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for
        placement test dates and details on registering for a placement
        test.

        A student who received a score of "3" on the Advanced Placement
        (AP) French exam is eligible to enroll directly into French 2A.
        A student who received a score of "4" or "5" on the Advanced
        Placement French exam is eligible to enroll directly into French
        100A; however, full credit will be awarded for French 2C if the
        student wants to take French 2C first for review.

        Students with credit for previous college-level courses in
        French, contact your home academic counseling office to
        determine the appropriate course to enroll in at UCI.

        Any placement exceptions must have the written approval of the
        French Language Program Director Professor Maryse Mijalski
        (mjmijals@uci.edu).

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Course
        Instructor to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading
        option of the class.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

                        Gender and Sexuality Studies

        Students registered in any course offered by the Department of
        Gender and Sexuality Studies are expected to attend both the
        FIRST and SECOND CLASS MEETINGS of the course or they may be
        required to drop the course electronically by the end of the
        second week of classes.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   German

        TO ENROLL IN A GERMAN LANGUAGE CLASS:

        For all German courses beyond 1A, placement testing is
        recommended for students who have had previous experience with
        or instruction in the language. Contact the UCI Academic Testing
        Center at testcenter@uci.edu, (949) 824-6207, or visit their
        website at http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for placement test
        dates and details on registering for a placement test.

        A student who received a score of "3" on the Advanced Placement
        (AP) German exam is eligible to enroll directly into German 2A.
        A student who received a score of "4" or "5" on the Advanced
        Placement German exam is eligible to enroll directly into German
        100A, 100B or 100C. However, full credit will be awarded for
        German 2C if the student wants to take German 2C first for
        review.

        Students with credit for previous college-level courses in
        German, contact your home academic counseling office to
        determine the appropriate course to enroll in at UCI.

        For placement-related questions contact Language Program
        Director Professor Glenn S. Levine (glevine@uci.edu).

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.
       _________________________________________________________________

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Human 1 courses:
  ~ HUMANITIES CORE (course codes 27600-28130):
  ~ For more information about the Humanities Core course
  ~     sequence, visit http://core.humanities.uci.edu
  ~ To ensure proper enrollment in both the Lecture and
  ~     Writing Seminar, students must enroll in the
  ~     Lecture (LEC) first, and the Writing (WRT)
  ~     second.
  ~ Students who did no take Humanities Core in the fall
  ~     quarter may enroll in Humanities Core for winter
  ~     quarter provided that they have passed the Entry
  ~     Level Writing Requirement. For more information
  ~     about Enrollment Policies, visit
  ~     http://core.humanities.uci.edu/index.php/enrollment-and-policies/.
  ~ Students who completed Humanities 1AES in fall
  ~     quarter but did not satisfy the requirement by
  ~     earning a "C" or greater MUST ENROLL in the
  ~     section designated 1BES, as listed below, and
  ~     earn a grade of "C" (2.0) or better in that
  ~     course.
  ~ Students registered in any section of Humanities Core
  ~     are expected to attend both the FIRST and SECOND
  ~     class meetings of the course or they may be
  ~     required to drop the course.
  ~ HUMANITIES CORE ADD/DROP POLICY: ADDS must be
  ~     effected PRIOR to the END of the FIRST WEEK OF
  ~     CLASSES.  DROPS must be effected PRIOR to the END
  ~     of the SECOND WEEK OF CLASSES.
  ~ Any exception to the two week ADD/DROP deadline must
  ~     be requested as an Enrollment Exception via the
  ~     online StudentAccess system after second week for
  ~     ADDs and DROPs and requires approval of the
  ~     Undergraduate Dean.
  ~ All authorization codes for Humanities Core sections
  ~     are obtained from Dawn Jenison (djenison@uci.edu)
  ~     in the Humanities Core office (HIB 182),
  ~     949-824-1964. Authorization codes will NOT be
  ~     provided by instructors in the individual course
  ~     sections.
  ~ Students enrolling in Humanities 1BS who did not
  ~     satisfy the requirement fall quarter by earning a
  ~     "C" or greater in Humanities 1AES MUST ENROLL in
  ~     the section designated 1BES, as listed below, and
  ~     earn a grade of "C" (2.0) or better in the
  ~     course.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Note that it is incumbent on the student to check the            ###
   ###  restriction status and seating availability of a course before   ###
   ###  registering or attempting to add or change their discussion/lb   ###
   ###  section enrollment.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINE TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS   ###
   ###  COURSES:                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Early deadline to add/drop/change    ###
   ###  grade option for any course specifically noted with a comment in ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an   ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  such courses.                                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: Deadline to add/drop/change grade    ###
   ###  option for all courses through WebReg. The Bren School of ICS    ###
   ###  STRICTLY adheres to and enforces this deadline for both          ###
   ###  undergraduate and graduate courses.                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2: The     ###
   ###  deadline to add/drop/change grade option is 5:00pm on Friday,    ###
   ###  January 15, 2021. After this deadline, students must submit an   ###
   ###  Enrollment Exception request online through Student Access.      ###
   ###  Exception requests will only be approved for extenuating and     ###
   ###  documented circumstances outside of the student's control.Fro    ###
   ###  more information:                                                ###
   ###  https://www.ics.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School WILL DROP ###
   ###  students who do not meet the required prerequisites from         ###
   ###  courses. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a course does   ###
   ###  not guarantee a seat in that course.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Priority for       ###
   ###  seating in undergraduate level courses is given first to         ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Graduate students seeking to enroll in   ###
   ###  an ICS undergraduate level course must submit a request to ICS   ###
   ###  Students Affairs. Note that approval is contingent on seating    ###
   ###  availability, and unauthorized students found enrolled in        ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Priority   ###
   ###  for seating in graduate level courses is given first to graduate ###
   ###  students. Undergraduate students seeking to enroll in an ICS     ###
   ###  graduate level course must obtain a written permission from the  ###
   ###  instructor before submitting a request for an authorization to   ###
   ###  ICS Student Affairs. Students should be aware that graduate      ###
   ###  level courses taken as an undergraduate will not count toward a  ###
   ###  graduate degree program.                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Students enrolling in courses through ###
   ###  Division of Continuing Education Programs may only request       ###
   ###  courses that show as "OPEN" in the Schedule of Classes. Approval ###
   ###  of requests is contingent on seating availability and            ###
   ###  prerequisite eligibility. For more information:                  ###
   ###  https://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                      Information and Computer Science

        RESTRICTIONS:All I&amp;C SCI courses will be initially RESTRICTED to
        majors in the Donald Bren School of Information and Computer
        Sciences ONLY. Some courses will be additionally restricted to
        specific majors or level(s) of standing.

        Course restriction details and the restrictions update timeline
        for all ICS courses are published on the ICS Course Updates page
        (http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php).

        DISCUSSIONS &amp; LABS: Discussion and lab sections begin meeting
        AFTER the first lecture unless otherwise specified by the course
        instructor. Always check for messages from your instructors
        before the start of instruction.

        Some lab sections are scheduled in laptop instructional labs,
        ICS 364A, ICS2 162, or ICS2 170. Students enrolled in these labs
        are required to bring a personal laptop to class meetings.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain an authorization code.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Note that it is incumbent on the student to check the            ###
   ###  restriction status and seating availability of a course before   ###
   ###  registering or attempting to add or change their discussion/lb   ###
   ###  section enrollment.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINE TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS   ###
   ###  COURSES:                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Early deadline to add/drop/change    ###
   ###  grade option for any course specifically noted with a comment in ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an   ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  such courses.                                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: Deadline to add/drop/change grade    ###
   ###  option for all courses through WebReg. The Bren School of ICS    ###
   ###  STRICTLY adheres to and enforces this deadline for both          ###
   ###  undergraduate and graduate courses.                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2: The     ###
   ###  deadline to add/drop/change grade option is 5:00pm on Friday,    ###
   ###  January 15, 2021. After this deadline, students must submit an   ###
   ###  Enrollment Exception request online through Student Access.      ###
   ###  Exception requests will only be approved for extenuating and     ###
   ###  documented circumstances outside of the student's control.Fro    ###
   ###  more information:                                                ###
   ###  https://www.ics.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School WILL DROP ###
   ###  students who do not meet the required prerequisites from         ###
   ###  courses. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a course does   ###
   ###  not guarantee a seat in that course.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Priority for       ###
   ###  seating in undergraduate level courses is given first to         ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Graduate students seeking to enroll in   ###
   ###  an ICS undergraduate level course must submit a request to ICS   ###
   ###  Students Affairs. Note that approval is contingent on seating    ###
   ###  availability, and unauthorized students found enrolled in        ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Priority   ###
   ###  for seating in graduate level courses is given first to graduate ###
   ###  students. Undergraduate students seeking to enroll in an ICS     ###
   ###  graduate level course must obtain a written permission from the  ###
   ###  instructor before submitting a request for an authorization to   ###
   ###  ICS Student Affairs. Students should be aware that graduate      ###
   ###  level courses taken as an undergraduate will not count toward a  ###
   ###  graduate degree program.                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Students enrolling in courses through ###
   ###  Division of Continuing Education Programs may only request       ###
   ###  courses that show as "OPEN" in the Schedule of Classes. Approval ###
   ###  of requests is contingent on seating availability and            ###
   ###  prerequisite eligibility. For more information:                  ###
   ###  https://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                 Informatics

        RESTRICTIONS: All IN4MATX courses will be initially RESTRICTED
        to majors in the Donald Bren School of Information and Computer
        Sciences ONLY. Some courses will be additionally restricted to
        specific majors or level(s) of standing.

        Course restriction details and the restrictions update timeline
        for all ICS courses is published on the ICS Course Updates page
        (http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php).

        DISCUSSIONS &amp; LABS: Discussion and lab sections begin meeting
        AFTER the first lecture unless otherwise specified by the course
        instructor. Always check for messages from your instructors
        before the start of instruction.

        Some lab sections are scheduled in laptop instructional labs ICS
        364A, ICS2 162, or ICS2 170. Students enrolled in these labs are
        required to bring a personal laptop to class meetings.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain an authorization code.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/XRLDYaofX7ovQs63BPTo to be cleared to enroll in ###
   ###  the desired course.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-units initially, ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. if you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/tyn2C5GiXLcCDfPsvmRC The School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences will wait to process requests until the 18-unit cap is  ###
   ###  lifted. No exceptions.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Friday, DECEMBER 11th by 3PM.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction,  ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Italian

        TO ENROLL IN A ITALIAN LANGUAGE CLASS:

        Italian placement testing is recommended, but not required for
        students who have successfully completed Italian classes in high
        school. Contact the UCI Academic Testing Center at
        testcenter@uci.edu, (949) 824-6207, or visit their website at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for placement test dates and
        details on registering for a placement test.

        A student who received a score of "3" on the Advanced Placement
        (AP) Italian exam is eligible to enroll directly into Italian
        2A. A student who received a score of "4" or "5" on the Advanced
        Placement Italian exam is eligible to enroll directly into
        Italian 100A; however, full credit will be awarded for Italian
        2C if the student wants to take Italian 2C first for review.

        Students with credit for previous college-level courses in
        Italian, contact your home academic counseling office to
        determine the appropriate course to enroll in at UCI.

        Any placement exceptions must have the written approval of the
        Italian Language Program Director.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

       _________________________________________________________________

                                  Japanese

        Students who want to enroll in a Japanese language class in
        Winter 2021 can get details about registration and dates of
        placement tests offered for new students via the UCI Academic
        Testing Center's website: http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu.

        For students who complete placement tests, oral interviews
        (one-on-one speaking test) will be offered from 11:00-11:30am,
        on November 20, 2020, on Zoom. It is on a walk-in basis and no
        appointment is necessary. Be sure to bring the survey form and
        test results with you. Your web registration restriction will be
        removed after the interview.

        For additional information, please call 949-824-6207 or E-mail
        the UCI Academic Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu. Students
        registered in any section of Japanese must attend the first and
        second class meetings. Any student who does not meet this
        condition will be asked to drop the class.

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Korean

        TO ENROLL IN A KOREAN LANGUAGE CLASS:

        Students who have prior experience with the Korean language and
        intend to enroll in a Korean language class for the first time
        in Winter 2021, MUST take a placement test. Testing is offered
        on November 18th. Students may register for this exam through
        the UCI Academic Testing Center website,
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu. For additional information,
        email the UCI Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu or call
        949-824-6207.

        After the test, appear for a Faculty Oral Interview to get your
        placement and obtain authorization to register for Korean class.
        Interview is offered via Zoom on November 24th, 1:00-4:00 PM
        (PT). Please email Hyunyoung Hyun, Korean Language Program
        Coordinator at hhyun@uci.edu no later than November 23rd, 12:00
        PM (PT) to schedule a time for interview. Please attach your
        language background survey form when you email Hyun. Be sure to
        get your student ID card ready at the time of the interview.

        Students registered in any section of Korean 1B, 2B, or 3B MUST
        ATTEND THE FIRST and SECOND class meeting of the course. Any
        student who does not meet this condition will be required to
        drop the class.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

        drop the course.

        Journalism Program to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the
        grading option of the class.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/XRLDYaofX7ovQs63BPTo to be cleared to enroll in ###
   ###  the desired course.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-units initially, ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. if you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/tyn2C5GiXLcCDfPsvmRC The School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences will wait to process requests until the 18-unit cap is  ###
   ###  lifted. No exceptions.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Friday, DECEMBER 11th by 3PM.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction,  ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

                                 Mathematics

        Refer to
        http://math.uci.edu/undergrad-courses/course-registration-and-placement-information##3
        for the Department's Add/Drop and Waitlist Policy. Many sections
        will fill to capacity, so plan schedules carefully.

        Please note: Being on the electronic waitlist does NOT guarantee
        a seat in the course.

        IMPORTANT: Refer to
        http://math.uci.edu/undergrad-courses/course-registration-and-placement-information#Top
        for additional information on Mathematics undergraduate course
        enrollment procedures. Graduate students have last priority in
        enrollment in undergraduate courses.

        Major restrictions will be lifted on Friday, December 18th, by
        12:00pm.

        REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat a course, please note the
        repeat restriction will be lifted on Friday, December 18th, by
        12:00pm.

                                 Management

        RESTRICTIONS: Due to the high volume of majors, enrollment in
        most Paul Merage School of Business undergraduate courses will
        be restricted to majors only until Friday, December 11th at 3PM.
        Some courses will remain major restricted.

        PREREQUISITES: If you received AP credit or transferred courses
        that are considered a prerequisite, please fill out the form at
        the following link:
        http://uci.co1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_cZp4lwCuDSY9cOh

        EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-units initially.
        The restriction will lift to 20-units on December 18th at noon.
        If you would like to enroll in more than 20-units, you can
        submit a form requesting excess units after this date at the
        following link:
        http://uci.co1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_50uWSu1PrugQQWp
       _________________________________________________________________

                             Fully Employed MBA

        DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Paul Merage School of
        Business is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM.

        ADD: FEMBA core classes are restricted to FEMBA students only.
        FEMBA students can add a FEMBA elective through WebReg.
        Non-FEMBA graduate students interested in adding a FEMBA
        elective course may contact the Program Office in SB1, Suite
        4200 or email femba-ps@merage.uci.edu. The deadline to add
        courses in the FEMBA program is Week 1 prior to the first class
        meeting. Exceptions may be made for students who miss the first
        meeting.

        RESTRICTIONS: MBA elective classes are closed to non-MBA
        students unless otherwise authorized.

        PREREQUISITES: Vary by class. Please check with the FEMBA
        Program Office in SB1, Suite 4200 or email
        femba-ps@merage.uci.edu.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the response General Catalogue under each course     ###
   ###  description. Most major restrictions will be lifted on a rolling ###
   ###  basis. Major restrictions will be removed/lifted AFTER the fee   ###
   ###  deadline. The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the   ###
   ###  right to maintain major restrictions on impacted courses. Check  ###
   ###  http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan for              ###
   ###  announcements.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite first, before          ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A.) If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form, and click submit. The       ###
   ###  student will receive a response within 3-5 business days from an ###
   ###  Academic Counselor.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate Engineering forms are located at                   ###
   ###  &lt;http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms&gt;                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE:Students earning a deficient grade in a          ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped after the    ###
   ###  first week of class.  Students should address any prior grade    ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE: If you encounter an enrollment        ###
   ###  problem please email engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule       ###
   ###  updates, restriction changes, and changes to course capacities   ###
   ###  at http://bit.ly/2020-21UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###  the Arts is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  After these dates, requests to Add/Drop are considered through   ###
   ###  petition based on extenuating circumstances, requiring the       ###
   ###  approval of the Dean of the school offering the course as well   ###
   ###  as the Dean of the student's major. Enrollment Exception is      ###
   ###  available on Student Access.                                     ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Note that it is incumbent on the student to check the            ###
   ###  restriction status and seating availability of a course before   ###
   ###  registering or attempting to add or change their discussion/lb   ###
   ###  section enrollment.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINE TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS   ###
   ###  COURSES:                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Early deadline to add/drop/change    ###
   ###  grade option for any course specifically noted with a comment in ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an   ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  such courses.                                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: Deadline to add/drop/change grade    ###
   ###  option for all courses through WebReg. The Bren School of ICS    ###
   ###  STRICTLY adheres to and enforces this deadline for both          ###
   ###  undergraduate and graduate courses.                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2: The     ###
   ###  deadline to add/drop/change grade option is 5:00pm on Friday,    ###
   ###  January 15, 2021. After this deadline, students must submit an   ###
   ###  Enrollment Exception request online through Student Access.      ###
   ###  Exception requests will only be approved for extenuating and     ###
   ###  documented circumstances outside of the student's control.Fro    ###
   ###  more information:                                                ###
   ###  https://www.ics.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School WILL DROP ###
   ###  students who do not meet the required prerequisites from         ###
   ###  courses. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a course does   ###
   ###  not guarantee a seat in that course.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Priority for       ###
   ###  seating in undergraduate level courses is given first to         ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Graduate students seeking to enroll in   ###
   ###  an ICS undergraduate level course must submit a request to ICS   ###
   ###  Students Affairs. Note that approval is contingent on seating    ###
   ###  availability, and unauthorized students found enrolled in        ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Priority   ###
   ###  for seating in graduate level courses is given first to graduate ###
   ###  students. Undergraduate students seeking to enroll in an ICS     ###
   ###  graduate level course must obtain a written permission from the  ###
   ###  instructor before submitting a request for an authorization to   ###
   ###  ICS Student Affairs. Students should be aware that graduate      ###
   ###  level courses taken as an undergraduate will not count toward a  ###
   ###  graduate degree program.                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Students enrolling in courses through ###
   ###  Division of Continuing Education Programs may only request       ###
   ###  courses that show as "OPEN" in the Schedule of Classes. Approval ###
   ###  of requests is contingent on seating availability and            ###
   ###  prerequisite eligibility. For more information:                  ###
   ###  https://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################
