   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###

   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###

   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###          School of Pharmacy and Pharmaceutical Sciences           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Department of          ###
   ###  Pharmaceutical Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops    ###
   ###  can be made in WebReg.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Department of            ###
   ###  Pharmaceutical Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can ###
   ###  be made in WebReg.                                               ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                           Pharmaceutical Sciences

        PREREQUISITES: Students who have completed the equivalent of the
        prerequisites at another institution may verify eligibility to
        enroll in a particular UCI Pharm Sci course by emailingthe
        Academic Counselors at PHARMSCI@UCI.EDU a minimum of three days
        before their registration window opens.

        REMINDERS: Courses must be taken for a grade to fulfill major
        requirements, unless the course is only offered on a P/NP basis.
        For PharmSci majors, BioSci 100 is the only exception and can be
        taken P/NP.

        Enrollment in discussion or lab may be required in addition to
        lecture. Choose from discussion or lab sections listed directly
        below the lecture.

        REPEATS: Students who wish to enroll to repeat a course they
        received a C- or lower in will be restricted from enrolling
        until noon on December 18th, 2020. MAJOR RESTRICTION: Students
        who are in majors other than PharmSci will not be able to enroll
        in major restricted classes (indicated with an "L") until
        December 18th, 2020.

        MINIMUM GRADE POLICY!

        Students must earn a grade of "C-" or above to advance to the
        next PharmSci core course. For example, you must earn a "C-" or
        better grade in PharmSci 170A to move on to Pharm Sci 170B.
        Please check the Pharmaceutical Sciences website for specific
        course requirement policies:
        http://pharmsci.uci.edu/undergraduate-students/.

        LAB COURSES:

        PHARM SCI LAB ENROLLMENT POLICY!

        THERE WILL BE NO DROPS ALLOWED OF ANY PHARM SCI UPPER-DIVISION
        LABS AFTER JANUARY 4th (DAY BEFORE CLASSES BEGIN)

        This deadline is earlier than the College of Health Sciences
        week 2 deadline.

        Lab fees of $75 are non-refundable.
       _________________________________________________________________

                              Physical Science

        DROP Policy:

        All drops must be made by the end of Week 2.

        Phy Sci 5, 105, and 106 are restricted to students in the
        following Schools: Physical Sciences, Biological Sciences,
        Engineering, or Information and Computer Sciences. Other
        students may enroll by instructor's consent only. For more
        information, contact the UCI Cal Teach Resource and Advising
        Center at 949-824-0689.

        WAITLIST: Waitlist enrollment and management is handled by
        WebReg, not by Instructors. More information can be found here:
        http://www.reg.uci.edu/enrollment/waitlistoption.html.

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Physics

        Please refer to the WebSOC frequently for updates concerning
        course changes, including adds, cancellations, and day/time/room
        adjustments. Please also visit
        http://www.physics.uci.edu/ugrad/affairs for answers to
        frequently asked questions.

        ADDS/DROPS FOR PHYSICS COURSES 2 THROUGH 99:

        DROP LECTURE, DISCUSSION &amp; LAB: The deadline to drop any Physics
        course is Friday, January 17, 2020 (the end of Week 2).  Drops
        must be made using WebReg. Students wishing to drop a course
        after that date must submit an Enrollment Exception via
        StudentAccess and obtain the required approval of the Dean of
        student's major. Approval is NOT guaranteed and is usually only
        granted in extreme emergencies. See
        http://www.physics.uci.edu/physics-enrollment-policies for drop
        policy.

        ADD LAB: The deadline to add a Physics Lab is Friday, January
        17, 2020 (the end of Week 2).  Adds must be made using WebReg. 
        This deadline is applicable to all students including
        ACCESS/Extension students.

        ADD LECTURE AND DISCUSSION:  The deadline to add a Physics
        Lecture and Discussion is Friday, January 17, 2020 (the end of
        Week 2).  Adds must be made using WebReg.  NO ADDS WILL BE
        ALLOWED AFTER THIS DATE.

        Students who wish to make a grade option change before January
        17, 2020 (the end of Week 2) should do so via WebReg.  Students
        wishing to make a grade option change after that date must
        submit an Enrollment Exception via StudentAccess.  Required
        approval is Dean of the student's major.  Send enrollment
        questions to physics.enroll@uci.edu.

        STUDENTS WHO FAIL TO FILE AN OFFICIAL DROP WILL RECEIVE A GRADE
        OF "NR" IN THE COURSE.  AN "NR" TURNS TO AN "F" OR "NP" AFTER
        ONE QUARTER OF ATTENDANCE.

        PREREQUISITE CHECKING ON PHYSICS 2: Students who wish to enroll
        in Physics 2 must be enrolled in Math 2A (corequisite) or have
        already completed Math 2A, or have taken and passed AP Calculus
        AB with a minimum score of 4 or have taken and passed AP
        Calculus BC with a minimum score of 3 or have received a score
        of 4 on the AP Calculus AB SUB. In addition to math, students
        who wish to enroll in Physics 2 MUST take the Math Assessment
        for Physics Placement Test (MAPP).Please refer to
        http://www.physics.uci.edu/mapp on the Physics and  Astronomy
        Department's web site or
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/physics.html on the UCI
        Academic Testing Center's web site for information regarding the
        MAPP Test.

        DISCUSSION SECTIONS:

        Enrollment in lecture and discussion is required. Most sections
        fill to capacity so students should plan their schedules
        carefully and enroll as early as possible using WebReg.  See
        above for information on how to add/drop a discussion section. 
        Attendance in your assigned discussion section is MANDATORY
        throughout the quarter.  No quizzes or exams will be graded for
        students who do not attend their assigned sections. See above
        for information on how to add/drop a discussion section.

        LABORATORY SECTIONS:

        1. Most sections fill to capacity so students should plan their
        schedules carefully and enroll as early as possible using
        WebReg.  See above for information on how to add/drop a
        laboratory section.

        2. Attendance is required Week 1, beginning January 6, 2020.
        Attendance in your assigned laboratory section is MANDATORY
        throughout the quarter. Students will be allowed to participate
        in their assigned sections only.

        3. Lab manuals for Physics 3LB, 7LD and 52A-B-C are available at
        the UCI Bookstore.  Courses 3LB and 52A-B-C also require the use
        of 5 blue books (grid) which must be purchased prior to WEEK ONE
        at the UCI Bookstore.

        4. LAB FEES: Students of Physics 3LB, 7LC, 7LD, 52A-B-C, 120 and
        121W will be charged a $25.00 lab fee.  The charges for these
        classes will be added to your ZOT Bill Week 1 of the quarter. 
        These charges will be posted Week 3 if you add a Physics lab
        after week 1.

        The last day to add a lab is Friday, January 17, 2020 (the end
        of week 2).  Students who drop a Physics lab course no later
        than January 17, 2020 may have the fee reversed.  In order to
        reverse the lab fee, students must bring proof of the drop date
        and their student ID card to FRH 4109, 9am-12pm Monday through
        Friday.

        For lab section add/drop information, see comments at the
        beginning of the Physics section.

        The Physics Tutoring Center is available to students in Physics
        2, 3, and 7. Please check
        http://www.physics.uci.edu/tutoring-schedule for scheduling.

        USING THE WAITLIST SYSTEM:  The waitlist system for all Physics
        courses will be activated through Friday, January 17, 2020 (end
        of Week 2). Placement on the waitlist does not guarantee
        enrollment in the class. Students still on the waitlist after
        January 17, 2020 (end of week 2) will not be added via the
        waitlist system.  If you are unable to add through the waitlist
        system, you must add an open section using WebReg by the
        enrollment deadline - Friday, January 17, 2020 (end of week 2).

        Visit http://www.reg.uci.edu/enrollment/waitlistoption.html for
        more information regarding the waitlist system.
       _________________________________________________________________

Physics course numbers 200 - 299:
  ~ Undergraduates may take Physics courses numbered 200
  ~     and higher provided (1) their overall GPA is 3.0
  ~     or better, (2) their GPA in Physics courses is
  ~     3.5 or better, (3) they have the approval of the
  ~     Physics Dept. Undergraduate Committee and (4)
  ~     approval of the Department's Committee on
  ~     Graduate Affairs.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Ecology is Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in      ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  Friday Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social Ecology ###
   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL &amp; MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FIELD STUDY: Students are encouraged to begin planning for Field ###
   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following web site: ###
   ###  http://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-procedures      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact the    ###
   ###  instructor of the course.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some School of Social ###
   ###  Ecology courses will be restricted to School or majors only      ###
   ###  until December 11th at noon.                                     ###

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###

   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/XRLDYaofX7ovQs63BPTo to be cleared to enroll in ###
   ###  the desired course.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-units initially, ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. if you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/tyn2C5GiXLcCDfPsvmRC The School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences will wait to process requests until the 18-unit cap is  ###
   ###  lifted. No exceptions.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Friday, DECEMBER 11th by 3PM.               ###

   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     Program in Public Health                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Program in Public      ###
   ###  Health is the Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in   ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the Program in Public Health is Friday  ###
   ###  of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable units   ###
   ###  beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student                 ###
   ###  Access/Enrollment Exceptions.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Program in Public Health ###
   ###  is the Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.   ###
   ###  Students are responsible for all materials from the start of the ###
   ###  term. Failure to take any exams or quizzes, even those given     ###
   ###  before you have added the course, will result in a zero score    ###
   ###  for each quiz or exam.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDITIONAL UNITS: If you wish to enroll in more than 18 units,   ###
   ###  please be aware, the Student Affairs Office will not do this     ###
   ###  until the University restriction has been lifted, which will be  ###
   ###  on December 18. After that date, students will be able to enroll ###
   ###  in up to 20 units. For more than 20 units, please contact        ###
   ###  phuao@uci.edu on or after December 18.                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                Public Health

        Public Health course offerings/times/days/locations are subject
        to change without notice. Check WebSOC for the latest updates.

        IMPORTANT: Refer to the Public Health Student Affairs Office or
        the Public Health website at: http://publichealth.uci.edu/ for
        additional information on Public Health course enrollment
        procedures and frequently asked questions, policies, and contact
        information.

        PREREQUISITES: Prerequisites may be cleared ahead of your
        registration date. Please e-mail Public Health Undergraduate
        Student Affairs at: phuao@uci.edu a minimum of one week before
        your registration window opens. If you received AP credit for
        Statistics of took Statistics at another institution, you may
        need clearance to enroll in Public Health 101. Please e-mail
        Public Health Undergraduate Student Affairs at: phuao@uci.edu a
        minimum of one week before your registration window opens to
        obtain clearance.

        REMINDERS: Courses must be taken for a letter grade to fulfill
        major requirements. Enrollment in discussion or lab may be
        required in addition to lecture. Choose from discussion or lab
        sections listed directly below the lecture.

        PRACTICUM: Undergraduate students must begin preparing for
        Practicum one to two quarters in advance. For information on
        procedures and deadlines, please visit:
        http://publichealth.uci.edu/ph/_app_undergraduate_practicum/procedures_deadlines.

        Please contact phpracticum@uci.edu with any questions regarding
        Practicum course enrollment.

        MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in
        some Public Health courses will be restricted to Public Health
        majors only. Major restrictions will be lifted on December 18 at
        noon.

        AUTHORIZATION CODES:  Contact instructor or phuao@uci.edu,
        unless otherwise noted.

        WAITLIST: Placement on the waitlist does not guarantee
        enrollment in the class.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Ecology                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Ecology is Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in      ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  Friday Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social Ecology ###
   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL &amp; MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FIELD STUDY: Students are encouraged to begin planning for Field ###
   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following web site: ###
   ###  http://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-procedures      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact the    ###
   ###  instructor of the course.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some School of Social ###
   ###  Ecology courses will be restricted to School or majors only      ###
   ###  until December 11th at noon.                                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

SocEcol  195       FIELD STUDY
      ~ Field Study
      ~ Social Ecology 195 enrollment requires that students have formally
      ~    accepted a placement offer from a field study site and submitted a
      ~    course enrollment form by the appropriate deadline. For more
      ~    information about the process and deadlines apply to Fiel Study go
      ~    to https://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-procedures
      ~ SocEcol 195 is P/NP only. Field Study is a variable unit course. Enroll
      ~    via WebReg entering the appropriate number of units needed (1
      ~    unit/25 hours of field work).
      ~ The Field Study Areas listed below reflect faculty departmental
      ~    affiliations and provide students with a general guideline with
      ~    which to select a Field Study course section. It is recommended (but
      ~    NOT required) that students match their field placement site with a
      ~    course section in the appropriate area.
      ~ C sections are CLS Faculty
      ~ P sections are PSCI Faculty
      ~ U sections are UPPP Faculty
      ~ For more information on the difference between 195 and 195W go to:
      ~    https://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/pages/195-vs-195w
    CCode Typ Sec Unt  Instructor         Time              Place       Final                      Max     Enr      WL Req Rstr Status

SocEcol  195W      FS WRITING SEMINAR
      ~ FS Writing Seminar
      ~ Social Ecology 195W enrollment requires that students have formally
      ~    accepted a placement offer from a field study site and submitted a
      ~    course enrollment form by the appropriate deadline. For more
      ~    information about the process and deadlines to apply to Field Study
      ~    go to https://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-procedure
      ~ All students who meet the course enrollment from deadline and
      ~    prerequisites will be guaranteed a spot in SocEcol 195, Traditional
      ~    Field Study. Enrollment in SocEcol 195W is NOT guaranteed as demand
      ~    exceeds seats available. Students will be able to enroll during
      ~    their enrollment window and oce 195W is full, students will need to
      ~    enroll in 195. There are other classes that can fulfill upper
      ~    division writing.
      ~ SocEcol 195W must be taken for a letter grade. Field Study Writing
      ~    Seminar is a variable unit course. Enroll via WebReg entering the
      ~    appropriate number of units needed (1 unit/25 hours of field work).
      ~ The Field Study Ara listed below reflect faculty departmental
      ~    affiliations and provide students with a general guideline with
      ~    which to select a Field Study course section. It is recommended (but
      ~    NOT required) that students match their field placement site with a
      ~    course section in the appropriate area.
      ~ C sections are for CLS Faculty.
      ~ P sections are for PSCI Faculty.

      ~ For more information on the difference between 195 and 195W go to:
      ~    https://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/pages/195-vs-195w

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/XRLDYaofX7ovQs63BPTo to be cleared to enroll in ###
   ###  the desired course.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-units initially, ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. if you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/tyn2C5GiXLcCDfPsvmRC The School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences will wait to process requests until the 18-unit cap is  ###
   ###  lifted. No exceptions.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Friday, DECEMBER 11th by 3PM.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction,  ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

                                   Spanish

        PREREQUISITES and PLACEMENT

        For all placement-related questions, especially regarding
        enrollment in lower division Spanish language courses, please
        consult the Spanish Placement Table at
        http://www.humanities.uci.edu/spanishandportuguese/language/placement.php

        Contact the Academic Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu, (949)
        824-6207, or visit their Web site at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for placement test dates and
        details on registering for a test.

        STUDENTS ARE REQUIRED TO ATTEND THE FIRST TWO CLASS MEETINGS.
        Enrolled students who do not attend the first two class meetings
        may be dropped from the instructor's roll. These students will
        be required to formally drop the course.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/XRLDYaofX7ovQs63BPTo to be cleared to enroll in ###
   ###  the desired course.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-units initially, ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. if you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://zfrmz.com/tyn2C5GiXLcCDfPsvmRC The School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences will wait to process requests until the 18-unit cap is  ###
   ###  lifted. No exceptions.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Friday, DECEMBER 11th by 3PM.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction,  ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Note that it is incumbent on the student to check the            ###
   ###  restriction status and seating availability of a course before   ###
   ###  registering or attempting to add or change their discussion/lb   ###
   ###  section enrollment.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINE TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS   ###
   ###  COURSES:                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Early deadline to add/drop/change    ###
   ###  grade option for any course specifically noted with a comment in ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an   ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  such courses.                                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: Deadline to add/drop/change grade    ###
   ###  option for all courses through WebReg. The Bren School of ICS    ###
   ###  STRICTLY adheres to and enforces this deadline for both          ###
   ###  undergraduate and graduate courses.                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2: The     ###
   ###  deadline to add/drop/change grade option is 5:00pm on Friday,    ###
   ###  January 15, 2021. After this deadline, students must submit an   ###
   ###  Enrollment Exception request online through Student Access.      ###
   ###  Exception requests will only be approved for extenuating and     ###
   ###  documented circumstances outside of the student's control.Fro    ###
   ###  more information:                                                ###
   ###  https://www.ics.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School WILL DROP ###
   ###  students who do not meet the required prerequisites from         ###
   ###  courses. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a course does   ###
   ###  not guarantee a seat in that course.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Priority for       ###
   ###  seating in undergraduate level courses is given first to         ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Graduate students seeking to enroll in   ###
   ###  an ICS undergraduate level course must submit a request to ICS   ###
   ###  Students Affairs. Note that approval is contingent on seating    ###
   ###  availability, and unauthorized students found enrolled in        ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Priority   ###
   ###  for seating in graduate level courses is given first to graduate ###
   ###  students. Undergraduate students seeking to enroll in an ICS     ###
   ###  graduate level course must obtain a written permission from the  ###
   ###  instructor before submitting a request for an authorization to   ###
   ###  ICS Student Affairs. Students should be aware that graduate      ###
   ###  level courses taken as an undergraduate will not count toward a  ###
   ###  graduate degree program.                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Students enrolling in courses through ###
   ###  Division of Continuing Education Programs may only request       ###
   ###  courses that show as "OPEN" in the Schedule of Classes. Approval ###
   ###  of requests is contingent on seating availability and            ###
   ###  prerequisite eligibility. For more information:                  ###
   ###  https://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

                                 Statistics

        RESTRICTIONS: Certain STATS courses will be initially RESTRICTED
        to majors in the Donald Bren School of Information and Computer
        Sciences ONLY. Some courses will be additionally restricted to
        specific majors and/or level(s) of standing.

        Course restriction details and the restrictions update timeline
        for all ICS courses is published on the ICS Course Updates page
        (http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php).

        DISCUSSIONS &amp; LABS: Discussion and lab sections begin meeting
        AFTER the first lecture unless otherwise specified by the course
        instructor. Always check for messages from your instructors
        before the start of instruction.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Note that it is incumbent on the student to check the            ###
   ###  restriction status and seating availability of a course before   ###
   ###  registering or attempting to add or change their discussion/lb   ###
   ###  section enrollment.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINE TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS   ###
   ###  COURSES:                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Early deadline to add/drop/change    ###
   ###  grade option for any course specifically noted with a comment in ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an   ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  such courses.                                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: Deadline to add/drop/change grade    ###
   ###  option for all courses through WebReg. The Bren School of ICS    ###
   ###  STRICTLY adheres to and enforces this deadline for both          ###
   ###  undergraduate and graduate courses.                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2: The     ###
   ###  deadline to add/drop/change grade option is 5:00pm on Friday,    ###
   ###  January 15, 2021. After this deadline, students must submit an   ###
   ###  Enrollment Exception request online through Student Access.      ###
   ###  Exception requests will only be approved for extenuating and     ###
   ###  documented circumstances outside of the student's control.Fro    ###
   ###  more information:                                                ###
   ###  https://www.ics.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School WILL DROP ###
   ###  students who do not meet the required prerequisites from         ###
   ###  courses. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a course does   ###
   ###  not guarantee a seat in that course.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Priority for       ###
   ###  seating in undergraduate level courses is given first to         ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Graduate students seeking to enroll in   ###
   ###  an ICS undergraduate level course must submit a request to ICS   ###
   ###  Students Affairs. Note that approval is contingent on seating    ###
   ###  availability, and unauthorized students found enrolled in        ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Priority   ###
   ###  for seating in graduate level courses is given first to graduate ###
   ###  students. Undergraduate students seeking to enroll in an ICS     ###
   ###  graduate level course must obtain a written permission from the  ###
   ###  instructor before submitting a request for an authorization to   ###
   ###  ICS Student Affairs. Students should be aware that graduate      ###
   ###  level courses taken as an undergraduate will not count toward a  ###
   ###  graduate degree program.                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Students enrolling in courses through ###
   ###  Division of Continuing Education Programs may only request       ###
   ###  courses that show as "OPEN" in the Schedule of Classes. Approval ###
   ###  of requests is contingent on seating availability and            ###
   ###  prerequisite eligibility. For more information:                  ###
   ###  https://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

		      Schedule of Classes    Tuesday, February 2, 2021

Search Criteria:
    Department: UPPP

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Ecology                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Ecology is Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in      ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  Friday Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social Ecology ###
   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL &amp; MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FIELD STUDY: Students are encouraged to begin planning for Field ###
   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following web site: ###
   ###  http://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-procedures      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact the    ###
   ###  instructor of the course.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some School of Social ###
   ###  Ecology courses will be restricted to School or majors only      ###
   ###  until December 11th at noon.                                     ###

   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

        If you have any questions, please contact the Humanities
        Language Learning Program at hllp@uci.edu.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system, and ###
   ###  requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean. For more            ###
   ###  information on the Humanities policy and adding and dropping a   ###
   ###  course, visit                                                    ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For more information on the Humanities policy on changing the    ###
   ###  grade option, visit                                              ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/grade_opt.php.  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php on    ###
   ###  the Humanities Undergraduate Study web site.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LAB FEE POLICY                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  A lab fee may be assessed for those courses using the Humanities ###
   ###  computer labs for class sessions.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment in lecture and discussion, lecture and studio,        ###
   ###  lecture and lab, lecture and studio and discussion, etc. is      ###
   ###  required for all courses offered by the School of Humanities, as ###
   ###  well as any courses cross-listed with a Humanities offering.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Writing

        PLEASE BE ADVISED

        Writing courses will have a "B" or "X" restriction starting on
        the first day of instruction. Students will need to contact the
        instructor to obtain an authorization code to add, drop, or
        change the grading option for the class.

        Waitlists for Writing courses will not be activated.

        ADD/DROP Policy during the FIRST and SECOND week of Instruction
        for Composition Courses

        Students who are permitted to add or drop a Writing Course after
        the first day of instruction must obtain an authorization code
        from the instructor of the section. Students WILL NOT be
        authorized to add a Writing Course after week 1.

        After the second week of the term students will no longer be
        permitted to drop except through petition.

        Students enrolled in Entry-Level and Lower-Division Writing
        courses are REQUIRED TO ATTEND THE ENTIRE FIRST CLASS MEETING.
        Enrolled students who do not show up on the first day WILL BE
        DROPPED from the instructor's roll and their spot will be given
        away. These students will still be required to formally drop the
        course.

        For more information about Composition courses and
        prerequisites, visit the Program website:
        http://comp.humanities.uci.edu/
       _________________________________________________________________
